About Us
The Tribe Story
The story of Tribe began with a transformative discovery of plant-based alternatives, leading to a deep dive into the kava bar scene across the U.S. The vision was clear: to create a space where people could unwind and enjoy unique, plant-inspired drinks in a relaxed, Tulum-inspired atmosphere.
From this vision, Tribe Tea House & Kava Bar was born. What started as an idea has grown into two fullr-scale kava bars in Kenneth City and Largo, Florida. Tribe offers more than just beverages; it’s a welcoming community where people come together, share ideas, and work toward their goals.
Our Products
Premium Imported Kava & Botanicals & locally sourced coffee & teas
Tribe takes pride in the quality of our wide variety of products. We enjoy bringing together products from all over the globe and local to the Tampa Bay region to create a unique menu experience for all our customers to enjoy!
Kava
Our Kava is carefully sourced directly from Vanuatu, an island in the South Pacific. Kava has an earthy flavor and a mouth-numbing sensation. We drink it to relax and feel a euphoric buzz. It’s known to help reduce stress and anxiety.
Herbal & Botanical Teas
Are you a tea lover? If so, you'll love the vast selection of herbal and botanical teas available at Tribe Tea House. Whether you crave a chai latte to start your day, a soothing chamomile to unwind at night, or our refreshing on-tap blue lotus tea, we have something to satisfy your tea cravings.
Coffee
Tribe Tea House loves to support local business! Caracolillo Coffee Mills roasts all of our coffee right here in Tampa Bay and is immediately delivered for brewing in both of our locations. Whether you are looking for an espresso-based latte, nitro cold brew, or a simple cup of french-press coffee – Tribe has you covered! We offer both dairy or non-dairy options with endless flavors to spice up your latte.
